In the above snippet,  is not an , much to our chagrin. Enter PEP 544, titled Protocols: Structural subtyping (static duck typing). The PEP solves the impossibility of defining magic methods for our classes. It defines a simple  class: once you inherit from it, methods defined in the class become eligible for duck typing, hence the name - static duck typing.from typing import Protocol

class Animal(Protocol):                           #1

    def feed():                                   #2
        pass


class Rabbit:

    def feed():                                   #2
        pass


class VenusFlytrap:

    def feed():                                   #2
        pass
