You learn a new programming language by comparing it with the one(s) you already know. Knowing a language's features is key to writing idiomatic code in your target language. Familiarize yourself with features that don't exist in your known languages: they will widen your understanding of programming as a whole.Originally published at A Java Geek on January 26th, 2025
